  "text": "LLVM IR-to-Machine-Code Generation Pipeline - Key Components:\n\n1. **SelectionDAGISel** (github.com/sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d, llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/SelectionDAGISel.h, line 45): Base class for instruction selection from LLVM IR to target-specific SelectionDAG nodes. This is the core component responsible for pattern-matching and translating IR instructions to machine code at the SelectionDAG level.\n\n2. **SelectionDAGBuilder** (github.com/sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d, llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGBuilder.h, line 96): Translates LLVM IR instructions into SelectionDAG nodes. Works in conjunction with SelectionDAGISel, taking IR BasicBlocks and Instructions and constructing the initial DAG representation before optimization and instruction selection.\n\n3. **ScheduleDAGRRList** (github.com/sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d, llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/ScheduleDAGRRList.cpp, line 138): Implements the Ready-to-Ready List instruction scheduling algorithm. This scheduler orders machine instructions while respecting data dependencies and resource constraints to optimize instruction throughput and latency.\n\n4. **RAGreedy** (github.com/sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d, llvm/lib/CodeGen/RegAllocGreedy.h, line 59): The greedy register allocation algorithm implementation. Allocates physical registers to virtual registers in the machine IR, performing live-range splitting and eviction-based allocation to minimize spill code generation.\n\n5. **MachineFunction** (github.com/sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d, llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/MachineFunction.h, line 294): Central representation of a function at the machine level, containing a list of MachineBasicBlocks that form the complete compiled function. Manages all target-specific machine-level information including register info, frame info, and jump table info."
}

